-- China to simplify rules for interbank FX market
-- By Koh Gui Qing and Shao Xiaoyi
-- Tue Dec 09, 2014 04:25AM EST
-- None



BEIJING, Dec 9 (Reuters) - China is simplifying the rules to allow financial companies to trade in its interbank foreign exchange market, its currency regulator said on Tuesday.

The State Administration of Foreign Exchange said in an online statement that the new rules are effective on Jan. 1.